# Claude Certified Architect: Foundations (CCA-F) Crash Course

<!-- <img src="images/cover.png" alt="CCA-F Crash Course Cover" width="700"/> -->

The first third-party exam prep for Anthropic's first professional certification. Four hours of hands-on architecture labs covering every CCA-F exam domain.

**Instructor:** Tim Warner | [LinkedIn](https://linkedin.com/in/timothywarner) | [TechTrainerTim.com](https://techtrainertim.com)

---

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.10+ and Node.js 18+
- [Anthropic API key](https://console.anthropic.com) with active billing
- Claude Pro or Team subscription (for Claude Code)
- VS Code with the Claude Code extension

### Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/timothywarner-org/cca-f.git
cd cca-f
npm install
```

---

## Course Structure (4 x 50 Minutes)

| Lesson | Topic | CCA-F Domain | Weight |
|--------|-------|--------------|--------|
| **1** | Building AI Agents That Use Tools | Agentic Architecture & Orchestration | 27% |
| **2** | Tool Design, MCP, and Claude Code | Tool Design & MCP (18%) + Claude Code (20%) | 38% |
| **3** | Prompt Engineering and Structured Output | Prompt Engineering & Structured Output | 20% |
| **4** | Context Management, Reliability, Exam Strategy | Context Management & Reliability (15%) + Exam Prep | 15%+ |

The exam uses six scenario-based contexts: customer support agents, multi-agent research, Claude Code in CI/CD, developer productivity tools, structured data extraction, and code generation. We build real solutions for each.

